SUMMARY:Montclair Music Club Concert - April 6th
DESCRIPTION:Montclair Music Club announces the April program\, Monday evening\, April 6th\, 7:30 pm\, at Presbyterian Church of Upper Montclair\, 53 Norwood Ave. This instrumental and vocal program presents a wide range of favorites including Donizetti arias with soprano Karen Lundry and pianist Barry Spatz; Gershwin\, Joplin and others by pianist Barbara Hause; a Poulenc sonata with flutist Carla Auld and pianist Tom Parente; a piano quintet with pianist Mark Yolleck and string quartet; and Samuel Barber’s lyric rhapsody Summer of 1915 with soprano Julia Rolwing and pianist Mark Cogley. Free and open to the public. Donations welcome. Reception immediately following the program. Enter the church on the east side of the building at the double doors. We look forward to seeing you there! \nMMC is a 501(c)(3) organization. Donations requested at the registration desk and/or the website: https://montclairmusicclub.org/donate/ Follow on the MMC FB page: MontclairMusic Club – Home | Facebook Find highlights of the 2025-26 season at https://YouTube.com/@MontclairMusicClub \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/montclair-music-club-concert-april-6th/
LOCATION:The Presbyterian Church of Upper Montclair\, 53 Norwood Avenue\, Upper Montclair\, NJ\, 07043\, United States
CATEGORIES:Live Music
